# Product ratings / custom aggregate tables

- **DDL**: `CREATE TABLE` for relational ratings (`ez_rating_criteria`, `ez_comment_rating_rows`, `ez_comment_rating_weights`, `ez_product_rating_rollups`) belongs only in `wp-content/mu-plugins/ez_core/database/sql/ez_bootstrap_custom_tables.sql`. Themes must not run `dbDelta` or ship duplicate DDL for these tables.
- **Domain & queries**: Use `EscapeZoom\Core\Modules\ProductRatings\*` — Eloquent models, Capsule transactions (`ProductRatingRollupService`), and readers (`ProductRatingSummaryReader`). Prefer **no `$wpdb`** in theme logic for these tables except at documented boundaries (legacy glue, debugging).
- **Theme role**: Hooks, AJAX/CRM callbacks, sanitization, loading partials. Delegate rollup/sync to `ProductRatingRollupService` via thin adapters (`Ez_Product_Rating_Rollup_Service`). Comment/post meta dual-write stays at the WordPress boundary only.
- **REST**: Public read summary — `GET /wp-json/escapezoom-core/v1/products/{id}/rating-summary`. Gate mobile/JWT via filter `ez_core_product_ratings_public_rest_permission`. Admin CRUD for criteria — resource `rating-criteria` under `/escapezoom-core/v1/data/rating-criteria` with filter `ez_core_data_rest_permission`. Do **not** expose generic CRUD or POST endpoints that mutate rollup rows from mobile clients.
- **WordPress core table names** (`wp_comments`, `wp_posts`, …): resolve once via `EscapeZoom\Core\Database\WordPressCoreTables` (thin wrapper over `$wpdb->{table}`), then query with Capsule — avoid `global $wpdb` scattered in themes for name resolution.
- **Diagnostics only**: `EscapeZoom\Core\Database\WordPressQueryCounter::current()` for `$wpdb->num_queries` style profiling — not domain data.
